### New `TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds` overload with single parameter

The [TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(Int64, Int64)](/en-us/dotnet/api/system.timespan.frommilliseconds#system-timespan-frommilliseconds\(system-int64-system-int64\)) method was introduced previously without adding an overload that takes a single parameter.

Although this works since the second parameter is optional, it causes a compilation error when used in a LINQ expression like:

```
